  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dominica Tropical Storm Erika 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A tropical storm heading across the Caribbean has killed at least 20 people on the island of Dominica with dozens more missing. Tropical Storm Erika caused floods and mudslides that have set the country back 20 years its prime minister said. Erika later hit the Dominican Republic and Haiti with high winds and heavy rain but experts said it was weakening. At least 31 people on the island of 72 000 people have been reported missing according to officials with the Barbados-based Caribbean Disaster Emergency Response Agency. Island Electricity and water supplies were gradually being restored but shops were still closed.</narrative>
  </description>
